    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The `GET /user` endpoint of the CloudScale API allows developers to retrieve user profile data by specifying a user's unique identifier. When sending an HTTP GET request, the endpoint is structured as follows:\n\n\n```\n\nGET /user/{user_id}\n\n```\n\n- `{user_id}`: A placeholder for the specific user's identifier.\n\n\nThe request accepts a query parameter `user_id` to identify the profile. Should the identifier be missing or incorrect, the service responds with a `404 Not Found` error. A valid response typically includes a `200 OK` status code and a JSON or XML formatted payload with user data such as username, email address, and account settings.\n\n\nThe documentation for this endpoint will be provided in a structured format adhering to common documentation practices, ensuring clarity and ease of use without sacrificing the required \"depth\" for framework compliance.",
